24 (2) The sponsoring legislator must provide the completed form
25 required under subsection (1) to the department. The department
26 must provide the completed form to the chairpersons of the senate
27 and house of representatives appropriations committees, senate
28 fiscal agency, and house fiscal agency.
29 (3) A for-profit business is not eligible to receive an
SCS H01298'25 (H-2) usken3

4
1 enhancement grant. A nonprofit organization is eligible for an
2 enhancement grant only if it meets all of the following
3 requirements:
4 (a) Has continuously operated in this state for the preceding
5 36 months.
6 (b) Has had a physical office in this state for not less than
7 the preceding 12 consecutive months.
8 (c) Has a board of directors.
9 (4) An enhancement grant must not be used to pay a tax lien,
10 delinquent tax, or other obligation owed to this state.
11 (5) The department shall develop a webpage on the department's
12 official website to display the completed public disclosures
13 required under subsection (1). The webpage developed under this
14 subsection must be conspicuously available to the public. The
15 department shall post the completed public disclosures on the
16 webpage not later than the following, as applicable:
17 (a) For the calendar year 2026, 10 business days after the
18 development of the webpage.
19 (b) 10 business days after the department's receipt of the
20 complete public disclosure.
21 (6) Not later than 30 days after an enhancement grant is
22 appropriated to a state agency, the department shall update the
23 public webpage created in subsection (5) to include the amount of
24 funding that was appropriated for the enhancement grant and the
25 status of the funding.
26 (7) Not later than 30 days after an enhancement grant is
27 appropriated to a nonprofit organization, the nonprofit shall
28 provide its internal revenue service form 990, 990-EZ, or other
29 990-series return for the most recent tax year to the department.
SCS H01298'25 (H-2) usken3

5
1 Not later 10 business days after receipt of the form, the
2 department shall post, to the extent permitted by law, the form to
3 the public webpage created in subsection (5).
4 (8) As used in this section:
5 (a) "Enhancement grant" means an appropriation that authorizes
6 or obligates a specific amount of money for a contract, grant,
7 loan, or other economic assistance, incentive, or expenditure to a
8 specific person, organization, unit of local government, or project
9 or activity in a unit of local government, other than through a
10 formula-driven or competitive award process.
11 (b) "Immediate family member" means any of the following
12 individuals:
13 (i) An individual's parent, child, sibling, or spouse.
14 (ii) Any other individual who resides in the same household as
15 the individual.
16 (c) "Legislator" mean a duly elected individual who serves in
17 either the senate or house of representatives.
18 (d) "Staff member" means an individual who is currently or,
19 within the prior 2 years, has been employed by the senate or house
20 of representatives.
21 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act takes effect January
22 1, 2026.
